stylometry: Fixed cost models are when you have set amount of costs and you are trying to determine how much of a product to sell at a set price to achieve maximum profit, or how many you make to minimize cost. An example of this can be if a company wanted to produce widgets for a fixed cost of $100 and a variable cost of $15 per widget. they are selling widgets for $22, how many do they need to sell to maximize profit or how many do they need to sell to minimize cost that would be an example of a fixed cost model. This model is trying to figure out what the best way to go about minimizing cost or maximizing profit and that is very important in a business so that you can keep it running and make sure you are making enough money that you can pay your employees, make money and still be in business.
